 Testing**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the javap instrumented output shows direct `Class.forName` calls, but the reflection-calls.json doesn’t include `OracleV1DOMAdapter.getDocument` for this method; it only has `class$`. It seems like the static analyzer might only recognize the synthetic class$ for `InputSource`. This leaves me wondering if direct calls aren’t being tracked correctly. Java 17 might preload static fields, affecting how things link. I need to examine if prior tests initialized the class and avoid reaching already initialized class$ fields. Coverage needs to hit these calls!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Native Run Limitations**\\n\\nIt looks like the native run isn’t functioning as expected. I'm considering that dynamic coverage might not be achievable through the tracing agent. Maybe I can try setting the static field to null before calling `getDocument`, so it accesses class$ each time. But the challenge is that this field is package-private static synthetic, which means I can't access it directly from my test unless I use reflection—even though direct reflection isn’t allowed unless mandated by a public API. It's a tricky situation!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_m60buummYQHRU8XicTsldVu8|fc_05b21ecbe08c151a0169fc80894fc88191b62571bea5a530cc", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jdom/jdom/1.0b8/gradle.properties"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1269, "output": 955, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38576, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778155638615, "responseId": "resp_05b21ecbe08c151a0169fc807771a48191a9dd30ec569312ae"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_m60buummYQHRU8XicTsldVu8|fc_05b21ecbe08c151a0169fc80894fc88191b62571bea5a530cc", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Optional explicit tested li